    <title>Implementing an own module</title>
    
    <para>
        Let us now see how to program our own module which extends the empty platform installation. 
        This example has already been done and is available <uri>https://github.com/panifex/panifex-samples</uri>. 
        How to run the module will be shown later, as well as what has to be installed to do that. 
        There are a few postulates needed to create a module:
        
        <simplelist type="inline">
            <member>Java JDK 7 or higher</member>
            <member>Eclipse IDE for Java Developers</member>
            <member>Maven Eclipse Plugin m2e</member>
        </simplelist>
    </para>
    
    <para>
        After running Eclipse, we will create a new project which is done selecting 
        <emphasis>File -> New -> Project</emphasis>:
        
        <figure>
            <title>Creating a Maven project - step 1</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="img04-create_maven_project_1.png"  scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" />
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </para>
    
    <para>
        Here it is vital to select Maven project. When we click next, we should get the following 
        screen:
        
        <figure>
            <title>Creating a Maven Project - step 2</title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata  fileref="img05-create_maven_project_2.png"  scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" />
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>
    </para>
    
